        "description": "The cold-classical Kuiper Belt Object 486958 Arrokoth is a contact binary composed of two flattened lobes, Weeyo and Wenu, closely aligned along their principal axes, despite each lobe having a highly irregular shape. The object's smooth and relatively undamaged structure suggests the observed bilob",
        "title_cn": "Arrokoth单次合并实现形状主轴配置的挑战"
      },
      {
